snippet.textDisplay:
About the 77th Golden Globe Awards hosted by
Ricky Gervais for the fifth time around, he did not disappoint; his remarks were
delivered just as biting and bitter as expected to those on the receiving end. I
have always found his “take no prisoners” remarks as entertaining as the king
of insult comedy once did, the late Jack E. Leonard. As for the show overall,
was entertaining from start to finish, for those of us that love award shows, I
settled down to watch, the next thing I knew, Mr. Gervais said good night, now
that is the only proof test of a show well done. Will Mr. Gervais be welcomed
back next year? This blogger and observer of current cultured television certainly
hopes so…Now, if I can just get those blond dye head female televison journalists
to wipe their wet dripping lips before appearing, I would consider my work half
done.
